## Team workflow

- Items are addressed as `sq <type> <number> <verb>` (e.g. `sq task 35 show`); create with
  `sq create <type>`. Run `sq <type> --help` / `sq <type> <n> --help` to explore.
{# Altitude rule: this cheatsheet is a cross-type SYSTEM MAP, not the full per-type playbook —
   one condensed line per type-role authoring pairing (who creates it + its single
   highest-signal handoff: parent/sub-entity/ref). The enter/do/handoff/watch detail for one
   type lives in its own sq-<type> skill; don't duplicate that here. Every fact below is
   derived by looping spec.items/authoring_owner/parent_chain — never a hardcoded type literal —
   so a dropped or renamed built-in type degrades gracefully instead of crashing. #}
